description.narrative:
1. Level of awareness and understanding of marginalized groups of rights and principles enshrined in Vietnamese Law (0-very little; 1-little; 2-moderate; 3-significant; 4-very significant) (measured by the Justice Index, independent review and oversight report).
2. Number of people who receive legal advice/assistance from legal aid providers (dis-aggregated by gender)
3. Number of laws and regulations adopted in response to specific recommendations of research studies supported by the project.
4. Improved access to court judgments (0-very limited; 1-limited; 2-moderate; 3-significant; 4-very significant)
* Revised indicators in November 2020 (Rider 3)
1. Percentage of communes/wards which qualify/meet the criteria in Decision 619/QD-TTg dated 8 May 2017, including on legal dissemination;
2. Number of cases in which legal aid representation is provided;
3. Number of laws/regulations reviewed for better implementation, supported by EU JULE;
4. Number of precedents promulgated
